<title>ITALY: Olivetti PC plant workers call 1-hour stoppage.</title>
<headline>Olivetti PC plant workers call 1-hour stoppage.</headline>
<dateline>TURIN, Italy 1996-09-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Union leaders at the personal computer factory of loss-making information technology group Olivetti have called a one-hour stoppage between 1200 and 1300 GMT on Wednesday, union sources said.</p>
<p>Unions called the stoppage at the factory at Scarmagno, where some 1,500 people are employed by Olivetti, due to their concern over the prospect for jobs at the company.</p>
<p>Olivetti said late on Tuesday it had decided to &quot;speed up the reduction of its presence in the hardware sector,&quot; which has been widely taken to mean it intends to exit the PC sector.</p>
